NON-COMMERCIAL USE
-----------------------

As the explicit author of this software I grant a permission to use it
in either an original or a modified form, free of charge and without a
need for an explicit permission, but only for a non-commercial purposes
and only to individuals (not to any kind of companies or corporations).


COMMERCIAL USE
-----------------------

If you want to use this software in a commercial application I can sell
you any type of license for a reasonable price. The price depends on a
type of your business and the kind of license you need.

If you can afford buying my time, I can also turn this code into any
application your business may need, as well as to provide you with a
professional support.

You can contact me at: tonikt@assets-otc.com



===============================================================================
The implementation of the native ECDSA speedup package btc/newec
is based on the code created by Pieter Wuille. The original code
has been significantly rewritten while it was being ported from C
to Go, but the author of the original implementation had obvious
contribution into the package's code, therefore please read this:
 * https://github.com/sipa/secp256k1/blob/master/COPYING

===============================================================================
Few parts of the source code (e.g. "btc/test/*.json") were taken
from the original (satoshi's) bitcoin client. Its license here:
 * https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/blob/master/COPYING


